verbose_text: Furthermore, dominant negative variant p.Cys885Ser HOIP and dominant negative p.Cys86Ser UBE2L3 did not completely suppress NF-kappaB activation, but reduced NF-kappaB activation to the level of response observed in control cells stimulated with TNF, in line with our previous observations on the effects of LUBAC deficiency.
evidence: UBE2L3 did not completely suppress NF-kappaB activation, but reduced NF-kappaB
